07/10/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Additional buffer zones have been established in southeast Turkey to prevent penetration by Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) terrorists from northern Iraq, the Turkish military announced on Saturday (October 6th).
The 27 new zones in Sirnak, Siirt and Hakkari are in addition to several established in June.
There were fierce clashes with PKK rebels in Van province on Saturday.
One Turkish soldier was killed in a PKK attack on an army post.
(AFP, New Anatolian, B92, Reuters - 06/10/07)
